description:
Pikachu's hurt and Red's missing--and only Yellow can help!

A strange yellow kid comes to Pallet Town looking for the elusive Pikachu. After befriending the irrepressible electric mouse and winning the trust of Professor Oak, this new Pokémon Trainer sets off on a journey to find Red--the most famous Pokémon Trainer of all time! Along the way, Yellow, Pikachu and an assortment of Pokéfriends battle a variety of nefarious characters--including the Elite Four, the most feared group of Trainers in the world!

description:
Dancers are young when they first dream of dance. Siena was six -- and her dreams kept skipping and leaping, circling and spinning, from airy runs along a beach near her home in Puerto Rico, to dance class in Boston, to her debut performance on stage with the New York City Ballet.

To Dance tells and shows the fullness of her dreams and her rhapsodic life they led to. Part family history, part backstage drama, here is an original, firsthand book about a young dancer's beginnings -- and beyond.

description: Adventures ahoy! Even cleaning up is an adventure when Sardine comes to own. Roaming through the galaxy with her spacefaring friends, Sardine is always up for vexing vile villainy and thwarting terrible tyranny. Ten of Sardine's wacky and wonderful adventures are told in simple, scribbly artwork in the sixth volume of this fun-filled series by Emmanuel Guibert....
